{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":642,"text":"People are living longer\nand societies are getting grayer."},{"time":5113,"text":"You hear about it all the time."},{"time":6985,"text":"You read about it in your newspapers."},{"time":8788,"text":"You hear about it on your television sets."},{"time":11158,"text":"Sometimes, I'm concerned"},{"time":12446,"text":"that we hear about it so much\nthat we've come to accept longer lives"},{"time":17078,"text":"with a kind of a complacency, even ease."},{"time":21943,"text":"But make no mistake, longer lives can --"},{"time":26249,"text":"and, I believe, will improve\nquality of life at all ages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33696,"text":"Now to put this in perspective,\nlet me just zoom out for a minute."},{"time":37824,"text":"More years were added to average\nlife expectancy in the 20th century"},{"time":44894,"text":"than all years added\nacross all prior millennia"},{"time":51825,"text":"of human evolution combined."},{"time":55275,"text":"In the blink of an eye,"},{"time":56827,"text":"we nearly doubled the length of time\nthat we're living."},{"time":61425,"text":"So if you ever feel like you don't have\nthis aging thing quite pegged,"},{"time":64752,"text":"don't kick yourself."},{"time":66090,"text":"It's brand new."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68627,"text":"And because fertility rates fell\nacross that very same period"},{"time":72802,"text":"that life expectancy was going up,"},{"time":76597,"text":"that pyramid that has always represented\nthe distribution of age in the population,"},{"time":82212,"text":"with many young ones at the bottom\nwinnowed to a tiny peak of older people"},{"time":87262,"text":"who make it and survive to old age,"},{"time":89523,"text":"is being reshaped into a rectangle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95468,"text":"And now, if you're the kind of person"},{"time":97300,"text":"who can get chills\nfrom population statistics,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":99681,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":100728,"text":"these are the ones that should do it."},{"time":102546,"text":"Because what that means"},{"time":104000,"text":"is that for the first time\nin the history of the species,"},{"time":107864,"text":"the majority of babies born\nin the developed world"},{"time":111658,"text":"are having the opportunity to grow old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117411,"text":"How did this happen?"},{"time":119438,"text":"Well, we're no genetically hardier\nthan our ancestors were 10,000 years ago."},{"time":123978,"text":"This increase in life expectancy\nis the remarkable product of culture --"},{"time":128822,"text":"the crucible that holds\nscience and technology"},{"time":132539,"text":"and wide-scale changes in behavior\nthat improve health and well-being."},{"time":139159,"text":"Through cultural changes, our ancestors\nlargely eliminated early death"},{"time":145467,"text":"so that people can now\nlive out their full lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149524,"text":"Now there are problems\nassociated with aging --"},{"time":152493,"text":"diseases, poverty, loss of social status."},{"time":154808,"text":"It's hardly time to rest on our laurels."},{"time":157771,"text":"But the more we learn about aging,"},{"time":159871,"text":"the clearer it becomes\nthat a sweeping downward course"},{"time":163934,"text":"is grossly inaccurate."},{"time":166954,"text":"Aging brings some rather\nremarkable improvements --"},{"time":170246,"text":"increased knowledge, expertise --"},{"time":174105,"text":"and emotional aspects of life improve."},{"time":180380,"text":"That's right, older people are happy."},{"time":184528,"text":"They're happier than middle-aged people,\nand younger people, certainly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188150,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":189356,"text":"Study after study\nis coming to the same conclusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192494,"text":"The CDC recently conducted a survey"},{"time":195350,"text":"where they asked respondents\nsimply to tell them"},{"time":198258,"text":"whether they experienced\nsignificant psychological distress"},{"time":201397,"text":"in the previous week."},{"time":202583,"text":"And fewer older people\nanswered affirmatively to that question"},{"time":206241,"text":"than middle-aged people,\nand younger people as well."},{"time":209866,"text":"And a recent Gallup poll\nasked participants"},{"time":212855,"text":"how much stress and worry and anger\nthey had experienced the previous day."},{"time":217658,"text":"And stress, worry, anger"},{"time":222231,"text":"all decrease with age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225607,"text":"Now social scientists call this\nthe paradox of aging."},{"time":228637,"text":"I mean, after all,\naging is not a piece of cake."},{"time":232091,"text":"So we've asked all sorts of questions\nto see if we could undo this finding."},{"time":237399,"text":"We've asked whether it may be that\nthe current generations of older people"},{"time":243341,"text":"are and always have been\nthe greatest generations."},{"time":246609,"text":"That is that younger people today\nmay not typically experience"},{"time":250301,"text":"these improvements as they grow older."},{"time":253227,"text":"We've asked,"},{"time":254575,"text":"well, maybe older people\nare just trying to put a positive spin"},{"time":258542,"text":"on an otherwise depressing existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260979,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":262750,"text":"But the more we've tried\nto disavow this finding,"},{"time":265627,"text":"the more evidence we find to support it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269546,"text":"Years ago, my colleagues\nand I embarked on a study"},{"time":271905,"text":"where we followed the same group\nof people over a 10-year period."},{"time":275017,"text":"Originally, the sample was aged 18 to 94."},{"time":278494,"text":"And we studied whether and how\ntheir emotional experiences changed"},{"time":281857,"text":"as they grew older."},{"time":283786,"text":"Our participants would carry\nelectronic pagers"},{"time":287121,"text":"for a week at a time,"},{"time":288646,"text":"and we'd page them throughout the day\nand evenings at random times."},{"time":291969,"text":"And every time we paged them,"},{"time":293783,"text":"we'd ask them to answer\nseveral questions --"},{"time":295859,"text":"\"On a one to seven scale,\nhow happy are you right now?\""},{"time":298948,"text":"\"How sad are you right now?\""},{"time":300457,"text":"\"How frustrated are you right now?\" --"},{"time":302632,"text":"so that we could get a sense of the kinds\nof emotions and feelings they were having"},{"time":306890,"text":"in their day-to-day lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309049,"text":"And using this intense study\nof individuals,"},{"time":312367,"text":"we find that it's not\none particular generation"},{"time":316245,"text":"that's doing better than the others,"},{"time":318530,"text":"but the same individuals over time"},{"time":321428,"text":"come to report relatively greater\npositive experience."},{"time":326311,"text":"Now you see this slight downturn\nat very advanced ages."},{"time":330773,"text":"And there is a slight downturn."},{"time":332434,"text":"But at no point does it return\nto the levels we see in early adulthood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338628,"text":"Now it's really too simplistic\nto say that older people are \"happy.\""},{"time":346669,"text":"In our study, they are more positive."},{"time":349828,"text":"But they're also more likely\nthan younger people"},{"time":352169,"text":"to experience mixed emotions --"},{"time":354366,"text":"sadness at the same time\nyou experience happiness;"},{"time":357007,"text":"you know, that tear in the eye\nwhen you're smiling at a friend."},{"time":361634,"text":"And other research has shown that\nolder people seem to engage with sadness"},{"time":366301,"text":"more comfortably."},{"time":367731,"text":"They're more accepting of sadness\nthan younger people are."},{"time":370639,"text":"And we suspect\nthat this may help to explain"},{"time":373256,"text":"why older people are better\nthan younger people"},{"time":376000,"text":"at solving hotly charged\nemotional conflicts and debates."},{"time":382000,"text":"Older people can view injustice\nwith compassion,"},{"time":386960,"text":"but not despair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389359,"text":"And all things being equal,"},{"time":391120,"text":"older people direct their cognitive\nresources, like attention and memory,"},{"time":395235,"text":"to positive information\nmore than negative."},{"time":398616,"text":"If we show older, middle-aged,\nyounger people images,"},{"time":401992,"text":"like the ones you see on the screen,"},{"time":404698,"text":"and we later ask them\nto recall all the images that they can,"},{"time":409885,"text":"older people, but not younger people,"},{"time":412268,"text":"remember more positive images\nthan negative images."},{"time":416652,"text":"We've asked older and younger people\nto view faces in laboratory studies,"},{"time":420814,"text":"some frowning, some smiling."},{"time":422714,"text":"Older people look toward the smiling faces\nand away from the frowning, angry faces."},{"time":429257,"text":"In day-to-day life, this translates\ninto greater enjoyment and satisfaction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436533,"text":"But as social scientists, we continue\nto ask about possible alternatives."},{"time":440846,"text":"We've said, well, maybe older people\nreport more positive emotions"},{"time":444524,"text":"because they're cognitively impaired."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":450876,"text":"We've said, could it be"},{"time":452131,"text":"that positive emotions are simply easier\nto process than negative emotions,"},{"time":455749,"text":"and so you switch\nto the positive emotions?"},{"time":458942,"text":"Maybe our neural centers in our brain"},{"time":461101,"text":"are degraded such that we're unable\nto process negative emotions anymore."},{"time":465572,"text":"But that's not the case."},{"time":467614,"text":"The most mentally sharp older adults"},{"time":470874,"text":"are the ones who show\nthis positivity effect the most."},{"time":474949,"text":"And under conditions\nwhere it really matters,"},{"time":477255,"text":"older people do process\nthe negative information"},{"time":479807,"text":"just as well as the positive information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482358,"text":"So how can this be?"},{"time":485876,"text":"Well, in our research,"},{"time":487957,"text":"we've found that these changes\nare grounded fundamentally"},{"time":491972,"text":"in the uniquely human\nability to monitor time --"},{"time":495213,"text":"not just clock time\nand calendar time, but lifetime."},{"time":499208,"text":"And if there's a paradox of aging,"},{"time":501670,"text":"it's that recognizing\nthat we won't live forever"},{"time":504696,"text":"changes our perspective on life\nin positive ways."},{"time":510204,"text":"When time horizons are long and nebulous,\nas they typically are in youth,"},{"time":515034,"text":"people are constantly preparing,"},{"time":517000,"text":"trying to soak up all the information\nthey possibly can,"},{"time":520779,"text":"taking risks, exploring."},{"time":523049,"text":"We might spend time with people\nwe don't even like"},{"time":526016,"text":"because it's somehow interesting."},{"time":528139,"text":"We might learn something unexpected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530359,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532443,"text":"We go on blind dates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":537277,"text":"You know, after all,"},{"time":538471,"text":"if it doesn't work out,\nthere's always tomorrow."},{"time":542121,"text":"People over 50 don't go on blind dates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544722,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":552014,"text":"As we age, our time horizons grow shorter\nand our goals change."},{"time":558342,"text":"When we recognize that we don't have\nall the time in the world,"},{"time":561358,"text":"we see our priorities most clearly."},{"time":564229,"text":"We take less notice of trivial matters."},{"time":566974,"text":"We savor life."},{"time":569140,"text":"We're more appreciative,"},{"time":570782,"text":"more open to reconciliation."},{"time":573461,"text":"We invest in more emotionally\nimportant parts of life,"},{"time":576315,"text":"and life gets better,"},{"time":579424,"text":"so we're happier day-to-day."},{"time":582305,"text":"But that same shift in perspective"},{"time":584269,"text":"leads us to have less tolerance\nthan ever for injustice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590061,"text":"By 2015,"},{"time":592137,"text":"there will be more people\nin the United States"},{"time":594799,"text":"over the age of 60 than under 15."},{"time":600019,"text":"What will happen to societies\nthat are top-heavy with older people?"},{"time":605363,"text":"The numbers won't determine the outcome."},{"time":609210,"text":"Culture will."},{"time":612203,"text":"If we invest in science and technology"},{"time":615332,"text":"and find solutions for the real problems\nthat older people face"},{"time":620184,"text":"and we capitalize on the very real\nstrengths of older people,"},{"time":626840,"text":"then added years of life can dramatically\nimprove quality of life at all ages."},{"time":633897,"text":"Societies with millions of talented,\nemotionally stable citizens"},{"time":638388,"text":"who are healthier and better educated\nthan any generations before them,"},{"time":643339,"text":"armed with knowledge\nabout the practical matters of life"},{"time":647189,"text":"and motivated to solve the big issues"},{"time":652296,"text":"can be better societies\nthan we have ever known."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659290,"text":"My father, who is 92, likes to say,"},{"time":663778,"text":"\"Let's stop talking\nonly about how to save the old folks"},{"time":667450,"text":"and start talking about\nhow to get them to save us all.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":673837,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675301,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}